				<td colspan="2"><span>Well, i'm a charisma junkey, so I have 285 charisma with a shammy buff :/  but anyways.
<br />
First off, don't worry about the lute that was said in an earlier post.  If you're pulling in a hard adventure, then you're using the silent song of quellious, and last I checked, that song is a singing skill...the original Kelins Lugubrious Lament was stringed.
<br />
Yes, I agree with Famka...I have learned to love my fading memories sooooooooo much in this dungeon, not just because of pulling, but those times that you'll just be THINKING of pulling, start walking to the door, and 50 things aggro you through the wall.  NOT COOL
<br />
Basically the only thing you can do it to see when you're able to single pull accurately, get fading memories..and buff the heck out of your cha.  Generally lots of CHA augs drop, and I dunno about where you guys come from, but on RN noone really wants them besides us.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
