				<td colspan="2"><span>I use a combination of mez, lull, and bind sight on hards alot. Bind sight can slow things down, true, but I like to be safe. Besides, it's the safest way to be able to target the mobs you want to lull without having to be in the room.
<br />

<br />
As far as single pulls... well, hards are really demanding on the group really. Single pulling can take some time, and as a result, can run you the risk of a failure. Best thing to do is as as posted before: Lull one, pull 2 using mez enroute. It's a delayed pull, and that 18 seconds or so should be enough to get the other most of the way down. </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
